[3.406, "o", "\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[0.005, "o", "/usr/bin/mysql_secure_installation: Deprecated program name. It will be removed in a future release, use 'mariadb-secure-installation' instead\r\n"]
[0.006, "o", "\r\nNOTE: RUNNING ALL PARTS OF THIS SCRIPT IS RECOMMENDED FOR ALL MariaDB\r\n      SERVERS IN PRODUCTION USE!  PLEASE READ EACH STEP CAREFULLY!\r\n\r\nIn order to log into MariaDB to secure it, we'll need the current\r\npassword for the root user. If you've just installed MariaDB, and\r\nhaven't set the root password yet, you should just press enter here.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.011, "o", "Enter current password for root (enter for none): "]
[37.764, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.044, "o", "OK, successfully used password, moving on...\r\n\r\nSetting the root password or using the unix_socket ensures that nobody\r\ncan log into the MariaDB root user without the proper authorisation.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "You already have your root account protected, so you can safely answer 'n'.\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\r\nSwitch to unix_socket authentication [Y/n] "]
[9.986, "o", "y"]
[4.943, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.032, "o", "Enabled successfully!\r\nReloading privilege tables..\r\n"]
[0.030, "o", " ... Success!\r\n\r\n\r\nYou already have your root account protected, so you can safely answer 'n'.\r\n\r\nChange the root password? [Y/n] "]
[2.581, "o", "y"]
[0.868, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "New password: "]
[14.119, "o", "\r\nRe-enter new password: "]
[3.985, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.039, "o", "Password updated successfully!\r\nReloading privilege tables..\r\n"]
[0.029, "o", " ... Success!\r\n\r\n"]
[0.004, "o", "\r\nBy default, a MariaDB installation has an anonymous user, allowing anyone\r\nto log into MariaDB without having to have a user account created for\r\nthem.  This is intended only for testing, and to make the installation\r\ngo a bit smoother.  You should remove them before moving into a\r\nproduction environment.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.003, "o", "Remove anonymous users? [Y/n] "]
[1.600, "o", "y"]
[0.573, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.032, "o", " ... Success!\r\n\r\nNormally, root should only be allowed to connect from 'localhost'.  This\r\nensures that someone cannot guess at the root password from the network.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "Disallow root login remotely? [Y/n] "]
[0.987, "o", "y"]
[0.582, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.033, "o", " ... Success!\r\n\r\nBy default, MariaDB comes with a database named 'test' that anyone can\r\naccess.  This is also intended only for testing, and should be removed\r\nbefore moving into a production environment.\r\n\r\nRemove test database and access to it? [Y/n] "]
[0.966, "o", "y"]
[0.551, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", " - Dropping test database...\r\n"]
[0.036, "o", " ... Success!\r\n - Removing privileges on test database...\r\n"]
[0.030, "o", " ... Success!\r\n\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "Reloading the privilege tables will ensure that all changes made so far\r\nwill take effect immediately.\r\n\r\nReload privilege tables now? [Y/n] "]
[1.023, "o", "y"]
[0.516, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.033, "o", " ... Success!\r\n\r\nCleaning up...\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\r\nAll done!  If you've completed all of the above steps, your MariaDB\r\ninstallation should now be secure.\r\n\r\nThanks for using MariaDB!\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\u001b[?2004h[root@salfa http]# "]
